From Steve Hollasch Subject Re What is the difference between Raytracing and rendering Zhenhai Li writes Hello I've raytraced and rendered and the only difference I've found is that raytracing takes a hell of a lot Am I missing something There are many methods of rendering raytracing is one of You didn't say what you mean by rendering so I won't Methods of rendering include o Pencil and graph paper doing the math by hand o Wireframe rendering of the projection o Hidden line rendering o Scanline rendering using Painter's BSP Z buffer Other o Raytracing o Radiosity o Holographic projection to film o Combination of any of the above Steve Hollasch Kubota Pacific Computer Santa Clara California